text: Oracle Corporation (NYSE:ORCL) has reiterated that it expects to generate about $65 billion in annual revenue by the 2026 fiscal year, a target first shared with investors a year ago. title: Oracle: A Growth Inflection Is Coming Into View
text: Oracle shares fell noticeably in the wake of a poorly received quarterly earnings report. My view is that the earnings report actually highlighted the potential for a significant revenue growth inflection in the near future. Oracle's cloud infrastructure, the transformation of its Cerner acquisition, and market share gains within its cloud apps business are key drivers for future growth.
